---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const profileHeaderStyles = `.profile-header {
  text-align: center;
  padding: var(--size-2xl);
}

.profile-name {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
}

.profile-role {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-md);
}

.profile-bio {
  max-width: 50ch;
  margin-inline: auto;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.stat-item {
  text-align: center;
}

.stat-value {
  display: block;
  font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
}

.stat-label {
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}`;

const profileCardStyles = `.profile-card-name {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
}

.profile-card-email {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
}

.profile-card-description {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  margin: 0;
}`;

const activityItemStyles = `.activity-item {
  padding: var(--size-m);
  border-radius: var(--radius-m);
  background: var(--color-surface);
}

.activity-item:hover {
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
}

.activity-meta {
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.activity-title {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: var(--font-size-md);
}

.activity-description {
  margin: 0;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
}`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Profile"
  description="User profile patterns with avatar displays, stats, activity feeds, and action buttons. Build profile pages and user cards for your applications."
  currentSection="examples"
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/docs/patterns/">Patterns</a> / <a href="/docs/patterns/application/">Application</a> / <span aria-current="page">Profile</span>
  </nav>

  <h1>Profile</h1>
  <p class="lead">User profile patterns with avatar displays, stats, activity feeds, and action buttons. Build profile pages and user cards with Vanilla Breeze layout primitives.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Profile patterns display user information in various contexts, from compact cards to full-page layouts. These patterns combine avatars, user data, statistics, and interactive elements into cohesive displays.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Avatar display with image or initials fallback</li>
        <li>User stats (posts, followers, following) with clear visual hierarchy</li>
        <li>Activity feeds showing recent actions</li>
        <li>Action buttons for messaging, following, and editing</li>
        <li>Responsive layouts that adapt to different screen sizes</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Profile Header</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A centered profile header with a large avatar, user name, role, bio, stats row, and edit button. Ideal for the top of a user's profile page.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/profile-header.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/profile"
      title="Profile Header"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="profile-header.html">&lt;layout-card&gt;
  &lt;div class="profile-header"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l" data-align="center"&gt;
      &lt;!-- Avatar --&gt;
      &lt;user-avatar data-size="2xl"&gt;
        &lt;span data-fallback&gt;JD&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/user-avatar&gt;

      &lt;!-- Name and Role --&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="xs" data-align="center"&gt;
        &lt;h1 class="profile-name"&gt;Jane Doe&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;span class="profile-role"&gt;Senior Product Designer&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;

      &lt;!-- Bio --&gt;
      &lt;p class="profile-bio"&gt;
        Passionate about creating intuitive user experiences...
      &lt;/p&gt;

      &lt;!-- Stats --&gt;
      &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="xl" data-justify="center"&gt;
        &lt;div class="stat-item"&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-value"&gt;142&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-label"&gt;Posts&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="stat-item"&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-value"&gt;12.4K&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-label"&gt;Followers&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="stat-item"&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-value"&gt;891&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-label"&gt;Following&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;

      &lt;!-- Edit Button --&gt;
      &lt;button class="button secondary"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="edit" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        Edit Profile
      &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/layout-card&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Profile Header Styles</h3>
    <code-block language="css" label="Profile header CSS">{profileHeaderStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Profile Card</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A compact profile card suitable for user lists, team member displays, or search results. Features an avatar, name, email, description, and action buttons.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/profile-card.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/team"
      title="Profile Cards"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="profile-card.html">&lt;layout-card data-padding="l"&gt;
  &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m"&gt;
    &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="m" data-align="center"&gt;
      &lt;user-avatar data-size="lg"&gt;
        &lt;img src="user-photo.jpg" alt="Alex Thompson" /&gt;
      &lt;/user-avatar&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="2xs"&gt;
        &lt;h3 class="profile-card-name"&gt;Alex Thompson&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;span class="profile-card-email"&gt;alex@example.com&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
    &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
    &lt;p class="profile-card-description"&gt;
      Full-stack developer with 8 years of experience.
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s"&gt;
      &lt;button class="button small"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="mail" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        Message
      &lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="button small secondary"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="user-plus" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        Follow
      &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
  &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
&lt;/layout-card&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Profile Card Styles</h3>
    <code-block language="css" label="Profile card CSS">{profileCardStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Full Profile Page</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A complete profile page layout with a sidebar containing user info and a main content area showing an activity feed. Uses <code>layout-sidebar</code> for responsive two-column layout.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/profile-full.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/users/sarah-chen"
      title="Full Profile Page"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="profile-full.html">&lt;layout-sidebar data-gap="xl" data-side-width="280px" data-content-min="50%"&gt;
  &lt;!-- Profile Sidebar --&gt;
  &lt;layout-card data-padding="l" data-sticky&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l" data-align="center"&gt;
      &lt;user-avatar data-size="2xl"&gt;
        &lt;img src="user-photo.jpg" alt="Sarah Chen" /&gt;
        &lt;span data-status="online"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/user-avatar&gt;

      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="xs" data-align="center"&gt;
        &lt;h1 class="profile-name"&gt;Sarah Chen&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;span class="profile-role"&gt;Engineering Manager&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;

      &lt;p class="profile-bio"&gt;Leading distributed teams...&lt;/p&gt;

      &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="l" data-justify="center"&gt;
        &lt;div class="stat-item"&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-value"&gt;89&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span class="stat-label"&gt;Posts&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;!-- More stats... --&gt;
      &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;

      &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s"&gt;
        &lt;button class="button"&gt;Follow&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button class="button secondary"&gt;Message&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-card&gt;

  &lt;!-- Activity Feed --&gt;
  &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l"&gt;
    &lt;header data-layout="cluster" data-justify="space-between"&gt;
      &lt;h2&gt;Recent Activity&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;!-- Filter buttons --&gt;
    &lt;/header&gt;

    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m"&gt;
      &lt;article class="activity-item"&gt;
        &lt;layout-stack data-gap="s"&gt;
          &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s" data-align="center"&gt;
            &lt;icon-wc name="file-text" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
            &lt;span class="activity-meta"&gt;Published a post&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
          &lt;h3&gt;Building Resilient Microservices&lt;/h3&gt;
          &lt;p&gt;Lessons learned from migrating...&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
      &lt;/article&gt;
      &lt;!-- More activity items... --&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
&lt;/layout-sidebar&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Activity Item Styles</h3>
    <code-block language="css" label="Activity item CSS">{activityItemStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Profile patterns use these layout elements and attributes:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <h3>User Avatar</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-size</code></td>
          <td><code>xs</code> <code>sm</code> <code>md</code> <code>lg</code> <code>xl</code> <code>2xl</code></td>
          <td>Avatar size. Use <code>2xl</code> for profile headers, <code>lg</code> for cards.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-shape</code></td>
          <td><code>rounded</code> <code>square</code></td>
          <td>Border radius style. Default is circle.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-ring</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Add a decorative ring around the avatar.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Layout Sidebar</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-side-width</code></td>
          <td>CSS length</td>
          <td>Width of the sidebar. Use <code>280px</code> for profile sidebars.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-content-min</code></td>
          <td>CSS length or percentage</td>
          <td>Minimum width before stacking. Use <code>50%</code> for balanced layouts.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-gap</code></td>
          <td><code>xs</code> <code>s</code> <code>m</code> <code>l</code> <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>Gap between sidebar and content.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Layout Stack</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-align</code></td>
          <td><code>start</code> <code>center</code> <code>end</code></td>
          <td>Horizontal alignment. Use <code>center</code> for profile headers.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-gap</code></td>
          <td><code>2xs</code> <code>xs</code> <code>s</code> <code>m</code> <code>l</code> <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>Vertical spacing between items.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Avatar fallbacks:</strong> Always provide initials via <code>&lt;span data-fallback&gt;</code> as a fallback when images fail to load</li>
        <li><strong>Status indicators:</strong> Use <code>&lt;span data-status="online"&gt;</code> inside <code>user-avatar</code> to show user presence</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive layouts:</strong> The sidebar layout automatically stacks on smaller screens when content-min is reached</li>
        <li><strong>Activity loading:</strong> Consider pagination or infinite scroll for long activity feeds to improve performance</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Ensure avatar images have meaningful <code>alt</code> text and buttons have clear labels</li>
        <li><strong>Stats formatting:</strong> Use abbreviated numbers (e.g., 12.4K) for large counts to maintain visual balance</li>
        <li><strong>Sticky sidebar:</strong> Use <code>data-sticky</code> on the sidebar card to keep profile info visible while scrolling</li>
        <li><strong>Empty states:</strong> Provide helpful messages when activity feeds are empty</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

